<br>
The problem is, that at the moment, while I think Crylin is irritating, he hasn't really done anything to warrant banning asside from as you said, the rant material in general.<br>
<br>
I'd definitley agree that if he continues posting blatant rant material outside of rants, it is bannable, and I think the rest of the mods would probably deal with it relativley quickly.<br>
<br>
<br>
In response to the threadjacking side of it, I'd definitley agree that this is part of ranting, and in all seriousness, I don't think the moderators will pick up on any one for threadjacking. There isn't really anyone who is using threadjacking excessivley, even when it does occour, it's more of a meander than a threadjack. So don't feel worried about threadjacking a post.<br>
<br>
What happens, is if threadjacking is part of a consistant effort to disrupt (for instance, if someone decided to launch into rants about myself in several unrelated posts, as well as starting multiple threads about it) it does need to be taken into consideration.<br>
<br>
The problem is that Crylin comes across as intending to disrupt the board, but has not really successfully done so (not nearly as bad as Ixitx or as much as Kwip). Although I can appreciate that some may think that he has.<br>
<br>
Because his motivation is in question, and the actual stuff he's done isn't too bad in the scheme of things, what we've done is put down a clear line in the sand so that if he is actually intending to be disruptive, he will cross it, and we'll know. If he isn't intending to be disruptive, it's easy enough for him not to be disruptive and we'll know that too. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://216.94.170.106/phpBB2/images/avatars/19834029863f67d57cdd2ec.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
