<br>
While I on a personal level would love to ban Crylin, in all honesty it just comes from dettesting his rant material. <br>
<br>
Now, the problem is that while I can see what you mean about him being a pest, I don't want to act unless he actually disrupts the forums. If we were to ban him for something as arbitrarily as not liking him, it opens up a metaphorical can of worms, as there are a thousand and one other people I dettest here.<br>
<br>
But, in the last few days, Crylin has edged over the line towards disruption, while not outright disrupting the forums, the stuff he's been saying, and the way he's been saying it has indicated that his purpose is to disrupt.<br>
<br>
Now, if we (the moderators) knew that for certain, he would undoubtedly be gone by now, in fact there was some discussion about it.<br>
<br>
Instead, partly because of this, but mostly because in terms of what he's done, he's not really gone right over the line, we've decided upon this particular course of action.<br>
<br>
Now, we are no longer giving him as much lee-way as I think we'd give every other single member here.  <br>
<br>
This means he'll have to tone himself down a lot to stay. <br>
<br>
Now, there are two outcomes of this decision, both of which are down to Crylin.<br>
<br>
1.) Crylin calms down, he is somewhat contained because what he can get away with is restricted, in which case he is no longer a major problem.<br>
<br>
2.) Crylin doesn't calm down, he carrys on, and in a few days gets banned.<br>
<br>
Either way, it'll leave us the moderators in absolutley no doubt as to Crylin's intentions. And while I'd hate to admit it, I'm not certain if Crylin is just trying to see how far he can push us, or if he really wants to disrupt the board.<br>
<br>
<br>
Either way, the problem will be resolved one way or the other.<br>
<br>
Essentially.<br>
<br>
I'm pretty much refusing to moderate on the grounds of content, unless that content is part of a consistent attempt to disrupt the forum, either by stupidity, or malliciousness.<br>
<br>
Now, while I do think he is a pest, he has not really demonstrated (in my mind) malliciousness, nor the stupidity I mean (By stupidity I mean ignoring the guidelines we have set down for him)<br>
<br>
This is what this decision is intended to do.<br>
<br>
Hope that makes a little more sense Tib <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
